702627f-a.title: Brooklyn: 19th Avenue - 86th Street
702627f-a.text:
(1)
Eineteemth. Ave, east side, at the N.E. corner of 86th Street. A
visw of the Vag Pelt Manor, which once owned the surrounding land, under
a Dutch grant. It was at 1873-86th Street. It was bought by the City
of New York in 1925, for P4,000, and moved. Now 3-story brick homes
occupy the site.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
